Package: bayesianatoR
Title: Bayesian Reanalysis Tool for Clinical Papers
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R:
    person("First", "Last", , "author@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-ID"))
Description: Provides analytical (conjugate) Bayesian reanalysis of results
    reported in clinical papers. Supports multiple outcome types including
    two-group continuous outcomes, proportions, odds ratios, hazard ratios,
    correlations, and regression coefficients. Input parsers handle conversion
    between common reporting formats (confidence intervals, p-values, standard
    deviations). Produces posterior summaries, credible intervals, Bayes
    factors, and prior sensitivity analyses with 'ggplot2' visualisations.
